frameDefinitions: This frame contains words referring to teaching and the participants in teaching.
In this frame an  Agent preserves a Patient in order to prevent it from decaying.
An individual or organization, the Front, serves as a cover for an Illicit_activity or an Illicit_organization.
An Agent behaves as if they were a particular individual or type of Simulated_entity with the intent of misleading observers of their behavior.
An Agent, by virtue of strength or forcefulness, controls, rules, or strongly influences some Patient in some Situation.
Two individuals, the Subordinate and the Superior have a relationship such that the Subordinate generally follows orders given by the Superior and has the best interests of the Superior in mind.
frameExamples: Dad <t>taught</t> me that if you work hard, you will be OK - no matter what happens.
The laundromat is a <t>front</t> for the Yakuza.
The belfast bank robbers <t>posed</t> as police.
The fireballing righthander looked poised to <t>dominate</t> the Yankees yet again, striking out seven straight batters during one stretch
The archduke and several of his <t><fex name='Subordinate'>henchmen</fex></t> got out of the carriage, looking around nervously.
listRoleDefinitions: One who instructs a <fen>Student</fen> in some area of knowledge or skill.
One who is instructed by a <fen>Teacher</fen> in skills or knowledge.
An educational establishment, such as a school or college.
The area of knowledge or skill which is taught by a <fen>Teacher</fen> or to a <fen>Student</fen>.
A formal Qualification such as an academic degree or a certificate for which a student is aiming.
An action which the <fen>Student</fen> is able to perform as a result of instruction.
A guideline for correct behavior. In most cases, this concerns morally or socially desirable actions.
A piece of information that the <fen>Student</fen> is informed of by the <fen>Teacher</fen>.
Educational <fen>Material</fen>, such as books, tapes, or videos, used by a <fen>Teacher</fen> or a <fen>Student</fen> to acquire skills or knowledge.
A role, typically professional or vocational,  that the <fen>Student</fen> is meant to be able to fill as a result of their training.
FN: a program of lectures or other matter dealing with a subject
The time when the teaching occurs.

The <fen>Place</fen> is the location within which the teaching takes place.

Consider whether a possible <fen>Place</fen> phrase is really where the training took place or is rather part of a description of the <fen>Institution</fen>.
The <fen>Agent</fen> is the person performing the intentional act that leads to the preservation.
<fen>Medium</fen> is the substance in which the <fen>Patient</fen> might be  submerged to be preserved.
The <fen>Patient</fen> is organic matter that undergoes the preservation.
The <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Agent</fen> preserves the <fen>Patient</fen>.
The <fen>Place</fen> where the preserving occurs.
The <fen>Front</fen> acts as a legitimate individual, organization, or enterprise, but is truly a cover for an illicit organization or activity.
The existence and activities of the <fen>Illicit_organization</fen> are concealed by the <fen>Front</fen>.
The <fen>Illicit_activity</fen> of the <fen>Illicit_organization</fen> is concealed by (the activities of) the <fen>Front</fen> .
The time at which the deceptive activity occurs
The place where the fronting occurs.
The <fen>Agent</fen> is the person who acts in a misleading way to create the impression that they are a particular individual or type of <fen>Simulated_entity</fen>.
The type or individual that the <fen>Agent</fen> gives the impression of being.
The time at which the <fen>Agent</fen> impersonates the <fen>Simulated_entity</fen>.
The location where the <fen>Agent</fen> gives the impression that they are the <fen>Simulated_entity</fen>.
The <fen>Agent</fen> controls the Patient by being forceful and possibly aggressive.
The <fen>Patient</fen> is trying to gain control of a situation, but ends up being subject to the control and influence of the <fen>Agent</fen>.
The time when the domination takes place.
The place where the domination occurs.
The individual in charge of the <fen>Subordinate</fen>.
The individual under the command of the <fen>Superior</fen>.

My brother taught me <fex>not to be mean to guys when I'm not interested in them</fex>.
When I was two she taught me <fex>that a quarter was 25 cents and a dime was 10 cents</fex>.

Mr. Amber embalmed the woman in Turkey <fex>in 1922</fex>.
Mr. Amber embalmed the woman's body <fex>in Turkey</fex> in 1922.
Their role models might have dominated women <fex>in the past</fex>; they may not have understood the concept of equality.
Women tend to dominatemen <fex>at home and at Church</fex>.
